ianmag.com/smart-news/venus-flytraps-snap-their-traps-shut-in-less-than-a-second-scientists-say-theyve-discovered-how-the-predatory-plants-are-so-fast-180988949/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，叶子外层的细胞壁突然软化，使结构铰接至关闭位置</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 20:06:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/venus-flytraps-snap-their-traps-shut-in-less-than-a-second-scientists-say-theyve-discovered-how-the-predatory-plants-are-so-fast-180988949/</guid></item><item><title>纽约市艾滋病纪念馆用一束光来纪念这位伟大的美国雕塑家几乎被遗忘的遗产</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/with-a-beam-of-light-the-new-york-city-aids-memorial-honors-the-nearly-forgotten-legacy-of-this-great-american-sculptor-180988956/</link><description>一座新雕塑借鉴了斯科特·伯顿艺术作品的材料和想法，为城市空间提供了舒适感。他的最后一个公开系列是布鲁克林码头上的一组长凳和灯光</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 19:57:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/with-a-beam-of-light-the-new-york-city-aids-memorial-honors-the-nearly-forgotten-legacy-of-this-great-american-sculptor-180988956/</guid></item><item><title>“超级”厄尔尼诺现象已经到来。以下是它可能如何影响世界的天气和经济</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-super-el-nino-has-arrived-heres-how-it-might-affect-the-worlds-weather-and-economy-180988951/</link><description>专家表示，以太平洋温暖的表层水为特征的自然发生的气候模式刚刚开始，可能是有记录以来最强烈的气候模式之一</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 17:36:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-super-el-nino-has-arrived-heres-how-it-might-affect-the-worlds-weather-and-economy-180988951/</guid></item><item><title>“地球上最丑的鲨鱼”：首次在深海栖息地拍摄难以捉摸的哥布林鲨鱼</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/ugliest-shark-on-the-planet-see-the-elusive-goblin-shark-filmed-for-the-first-time-in-its-deep-sea-habitat-180988950/</link><description>科学家们于 2019 年和 2024 年再次发现了这些神秘生物，这是它们首次在野外被观察到存活。这些目击事件极大地扩大了这些动物的已知地理和深度范围</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://